講座教授











 


Gerald Cipriani
Prof. Dr.
 
Philippe Roussin
Prof. Dr.




 




Ph.D. in Leeds Metropolitan University, (1st Doctorate, Full Scholarship) UK
 
A researcher in French literature at the Centre national de la recherche scientifique (CNRS), I have been a member of the Centre de recherches sur les arts et le langage (CRAL), a laboratory of the CNRS and the Ecole des Hautes Etudes en Sciences Sociales (EHESS)


(a) Western aesthetics and art theory (b) Western phenomenological aesthetics (existential, personalist, ontological, hermeneutical, ethical) (c) Japanese philosophy of culture (The Kyoto School) (d) Dialogical philosophy of culture East/West
 
-Co-director of theseminar《Narratologies contemporaines》, EHESS(2007-2010)
-Co-director of the seminar 《Réévaluations de l'art moderne et des avant- gardes historiques;mondialisation des arts》,EHESS(2001-2005);






 







